290
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,450
Apparently,

291
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,840
Lu Yibo's psychological defense

292
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,700
has collapsed.

293
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,030
If he calls again,

294
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:02,410
he will definitely confess everything.

295
00:16:05,790 --> 00:16:07,190
Why hasn't he called yet?

296
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,340
[Lu Yibo]

297
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:27,960
Hello?

298
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:28,930
Chief Zhang,

299
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:29,870
sorry,

300
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,450
I was drunk just now.

301
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:32,650
You were drunk?

302
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,680
Is something bothering you?

303
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,320
You guys have been coming
too often lately.

304
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,390
Under too much stress,

305
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:39,600
I just spoke out of turn.

306
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,130
It's okay now, Chief Zhang.

307
00:16:56,870 --> 00:16:57,630
Lu Yibo, don't talk.

308
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:58,150
Don't talk.

309
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:58,880
Listen to me.

310
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:00,960
Cooperating with the police

311
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,350
is your only way out now.

312
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,600
I'll hang up.

313
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,069
You shouldn't have stopped him
from talking.

314
00:17:06,069 --> 00:17:06,920
He didn't confess yet,

315
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:07,829
and you just hung up?

316
00:17:07,829 --> 00:17:08,690
He's a drunkard

317
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,270
full of nonsense.

318
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,160
I'm not giving him another chance.

319
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,720
We will investigate it ourselves.

320
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:14,450
Chief Zhang,

321
00:17:14,550 --> 00:17:15,480
so charismatic.

322
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:16,680
There must be

323
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,960
some shady business going on.

324
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:18,510
How should we

325
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:19,710
investigate Lu Yibo?

326
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:22,920
I believe we can do it.

327
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:31,550
What?

328
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:32,300
Wait,

329
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:33,720
you even eat medicine?

330
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,700
Who are you talking to?

331
00:17:36,310 --> 00:17:37,510
I'm talking to the dog.

332
00:17:37,510 --> 00:17:38,680
Mr. Rong, I'm talking to it.

333
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,880
I'm scolding the dog.

334
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,650
I'm scolding the dog, Mr. Rong.

335
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,810
Take it to have some water.

336
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:53,400
So Lu Yibo said

337
00:17:53,850 --> 00:17:54,880
that night, Ye Jian

338
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,610
just asked him about the watch?

339
00:17:57,780 --> 00:17:58,910
That's what he said.

340
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:00,680
Do you think this has

341
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,410
anything to do with Ye's death?

342
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,240
My first instinct

343
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,840
was definitely still Bowen.

344
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:08,680
But it doesn't seem like him.

345
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:09,880
If it really were him,

346
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:10,590
he wouldn't have

347
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:12,250
a reason to swear at gunpoint.

348
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,460
What about Lu Yibo?

349
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:14,920
Look at what a coward he is.

350
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:15,920
He wouldn't dare.

351
00:18:16,030 --> 00:18:17,030
I mean, about Lu Yibo,

352
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:18,030
what should we do?

353
00:18:21,030 --> 00:18:23,160
The police are investigating him now.

354
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:24,350
That means

355
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,810
they haven't found anything on us.

356
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,400
If we do something to him,

357
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:31,930
we're simply asking for trouble.

358
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:35,200
Mr. Rong,

359
00:18:35,590 --> 00:18:36,750
forgive me for speaking out of turn,

360
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:37,590
but I feel like

361
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,480
ever since Ye died,

362
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,830
things have gotten
more and more complicated.

363
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:43,430
We really need to be careful.

364
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:46,210
We do need to be careful.

365
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,000
You tell me what to do, and I'll do it.

366
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:52,070
You go first.

367
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:54,110
Tell Bowen to come over here.

368
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:54,920
Okay.

369
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:18,240
Didn't we already

370
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,680
go through the Taobao records once again?

371
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,340
What else are you looking for?

372
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:24,640
I want to know why Captain Ye

373
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:24,550
[Vintage square student
male waterproof digital watch]

374
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:26,100
investigated this watch.

375
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:27,950
Captain Ye grew up with them.

376
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,200
He might have

377
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,530
seen this watch before.

378
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:32,390
Then why did he go to Fenglinwan?

379
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:33,830
How should I know?

380
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:38,010
Why did he go to Fenglinwan?

381
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:40,720
Why did he go?

382
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:44,880
Captain Ye

383
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,270
also came to review files yesterday?

384
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:46,590
Yes.

385
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,350
What kind of cases were they?

386
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,350
Cases that Chief Lu was involved in

387
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:52,030
the year before he passed away.

388
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:53,360
They are all right here.

389
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,260
Why did he want to check the files?

390
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,490
Because he found something.

391
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,670
[File Management System
of Sanjiangkou Public Security Bureau]

392
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:01,480
What did he find?

393
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:03,240
So what did he find?

394
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:04,670
What exactly did he find?

395
00:20:05,190 --> 00:20:07,710
[Anzhi Road, Sanjiangkou City,
Ping'an Province]

396
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:17,350
I remember Captain Ye

397
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,270
asked me to enlarge and enhance

398
00:20:18,270 --> 00:20:19,330
an image back then.

399
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:22,310
Zhang, I'm sending you a picture.

400
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,710
Enlarge it and make it clear.

401
00:20:27,790 --> 00:20:29,320
It seems to be just this one.

402
00:20:29,510 --> 00:20:30,570
Where is the image?

403
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,720
Let me look for it.

404
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,100
The truth is about to come out.

405
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,220
Sorry.

406
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:50,700
[Century Otto]

407
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,350
Bowen!

408
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:56,680
Bowen!

409
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,440
Stop yelling.

410
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,210
Let me finish this game.

411
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:13,200
Dear Mr. Botu Lang,

412
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:14,240
Reply:

413
00:21:14,310 --> 00:21:15,920
NHHU University

414
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:16,790
Admission Notice.

415
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,110
I know you are a straight-A student.

416
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,640
Stop showing off before me.

417
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,880
The Senate of NHHU

418
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,030
University

419
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,200
has offered you

420
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,680
the opportunity

421
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:26,350
to pursue...

422
00:21:26,350 --> 00:21:27,550
Alright, I know you're good at English.

423
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:28,160
Happy now?

424
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:30,350
Bowen.

425
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,270
Lang Bowen!

426
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,070
I've been accepted for a master's program

427
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:37,470
at a foreign university!

428
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:41,920
Pardon?

429
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:45,030
I've been admitted to a foreign university

430
00:21:45,030 --> 00:21:46,360
for a master's program.

431
00:21:50,310 --> 00:21:51,370
Which university?

432
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:54,040
Southern New Hampshire
Mountain University.

433
00:22:00,750 --> 00:22:01,270
You,

434
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:02,400
Lang Botu,

435
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:06,330
got admitted to an American university?

436
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:08,030
You don't believe it?

437
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:09,200
Could I be lying to you,

438
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:09,680
Bowen?

439
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:26,030
Bowen.

440
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:28,770
I'm okay.

441
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,500
I'm just too happy.

442
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,000
You...

443
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:39,130
You really brought honor
to our Lang family! I...

444
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,070
And I didn't fail

445
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:42,070
our parents' entrustment.

446
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:43,510
I didn't lead you astray.

447
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:52,880
Hello.

448
00:22:52,620 --> 00:22:54,840
[Century Otto]

449
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,060
We're looking for Mr. Lang Bowen.

450
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:56,790
Mr. Lang?

451
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:58,310
Do you have an appointment?

452
00:22:58,310 --> 00:22:59,440
He's here, isn't he?

453
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:02,240
Whether he's here or not,

454
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,240
Mr. Lang doesn't see guests

455
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,640
without an appointment.

456
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:06,310
Hello,

457
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:07,750
I am the Deputy Chief

458
00:23:07,750 --> 00:23:09,270
of Sanjiangkou Public Security Bureau.

459
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:10,750
We need to ask Mr. Lang some questions.

460
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:12,720
Could you set up an appointment for me?

461
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:14,610
Come on, you're a grown man.

462
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:16,440
I'm just happy.

463
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,200
Let's go to the cemetery.

464
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,310
Let's go to the cemetery right now.

465
00:23:20,310 --> 00:23:20,960
We must tell

466
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,200
this good news to Mom and Dad in person.

467
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:22,640
Okay.

468
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:27,440
Hear me out first.

469
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:28,930
Have someone

470
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,640
drive the car to the front immediately.

471
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:32,830
What?

472
00:23:33,510 --> 00:23:36,000
Tell whoever is looking for me today
to get lost.

473
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,460
Mr. Lang, it's the police.

474
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:41,540
Call him again.

475
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,440
Well, how about this?

476
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,270
Call him again.

477
00:23:44,270 --> 00:23:45,070
Tell him

478
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:46,000
that if he's really busy,

479
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,330
we'll meet at the Public Security Bureau.

480
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,070
Lili,

481
00:23:50,310 --> 00:23:50,880
well,

482
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,590
I'll get changed myself today.

483
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:53,960
And go help me

484
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:54,930
order 2 wreaths.

485
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,440
Get the most beautiful ones.

486
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,830
And write on the couplet:

487
00:23:57,830 --> 00:23:59,830
Lang Bowen fulfilled his mission.

488
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:03,310
Lang Botu brought honor to the family.

489
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:04,270
How nice.

490
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,580
Okay, Mr. Lang.

491
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,240
I'll go right now.

492
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,970
Get me the most beautiful ones,

493
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,810
as beautiful as you.

494
00:24:15,550 --> 00:24:17,210
Didn't I tell them to get lost?

495
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:18,690
Listen to me...

496
00:24:21,790 --> 00:24:23,500
Why didn't you say it earlier?

497
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,370
Let them come up.

498
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:32,350
Lili,

499
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,260
don't go buy the wreaths yet.

500
00:24:34,260 --> 00:24:35,510
First, go to the elevator

501
00:24:35,510 --> 00:24:37,240
and pick up some friends for me.

502
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,310
What's up, Bowen?

503
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:40,770
Nothing.

504
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,720
You... You should also go home

505
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,850
to change into something more formal.

506
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,110
We'll go see Mom and Dad later.

507
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:46,270
After I'm done here,

508
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:47,800
I'll go back and pick you up.

509
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:54,200
[Century Otto]

510
00:24:53,030 --> 00:24:54,030
This way, please.

511
00:24:59,310 --> 00:24:59,840
This way.

512
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:05,110
Hello, Chief Zhang.

513
00:25:05,110 --> 00:25:06,110
Hello, officers.

514
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:08,550
You're Lang Bowen's younger brother,

515
00:25:08,550 --> 00:25:09,550
Lang Botu, right?

516
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,000
Yes.

517
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:10,920
My brother is in his office

518
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:11,790
waiting for you all.

519
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:12,120
Okay.

520
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,240
We'll go meet him.

521
00:25:16,790 --> 00:25:17,810
Did you go

522
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:20,290
to Zhou Rong's birthday party
a while ago?

523
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:22,550
I went to attend

524
00:25:22,550 --> 00:25:24,790
Mr. Rong's birthday party with my brother.

525
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:26,090
Do you know what your brother was doing

526
00:25:26,090 --> 00:25:26,950
the next night?

527
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,260
Do you mean

528
00:25:29,310 --> 00:25:30,200
the night Mr. Ye

529
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,200
had the accident?

530
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:31,640
Yes.

531
00:25:32,110 --> 00:25:33,840
You remember it quite clearly.

532
00:25:35,030 --> 00:25:35,720
After all, Mr. Ye was

533
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,920
also like a nice brother to me.

534
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,960
Of course I remember.

535
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:38,550
Then what was your brother doing

536
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:39,410
the next night?

537
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,200
L-Let me think.

538
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,200
Go ahead and think.

539
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,000
Socializing,

540
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,070
working overtime,

541
00:25:45,070 --> 00:25:46,110
drinking, going home,

542
00:25:46,110 --> 00:25:46,630
or

543
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:47,880
hanging out for fun?

544
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:50,480
Chief Zhang,

545
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,650
what were you doing that night?

546
00:25:57,030 --> 00:25:57,570
Drunk driving.

547
00:25:57,570 --> 00:25:59,110
The citywide DUI crackdown.

548
00:25:59,110 --> 00:25:59,680
Yes, the citywide...

549
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:00,140
You see,

550
00:26:00,270 --> 00:26:01,000
it's been so long.

551
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,110
Didn't you also need time to recall?

552
00:26:02,110 --> 00:26:03,370
It's human nature.

553
00:26:03,430 --> 00:26:04,830
Have you recalled it now?

554
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:06,750
That night,

555
00:26:06,750 --> 00:26:08,400
my brother went back home quite early.

556
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,130
He was drunk.

557
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,530
And he didn't drive.

558
00:26:10,830 --> 00:26:11,790
Otherwise, when you checked for DUI,

559
00:26:11,790 --> 00:26:13,720
you'd definitely have caught him.

560
00:26:15,510 --> 00:26:16,110
Yangyang.

561
00:26:18,350 --> 00:26:19,000
Who is Yangyang?

562
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,400
My nickname is Yangyang.

563
00:26:21,110 --> 00:26:21,840
Chief Zhang!

564
00:26:22,590 --> 00:26:23,880
Aren't you here for me?

565
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:24,750
Why are you standing there chatting?

566
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:25,790
We ran into each other.

567
00:26:25,790 --> 00:26:27,030
-Chief Zhang, is there anything else?
-Go home, Yangyang.

568
00:26:27,030 --> 00:26:27,760
No, nothing.

569
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,280
Chief Zhang!

570
00:26:33,070 --> 00:26:33,790
Here we meet again.

571
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:34,160
Yes.

572
00:26:34,180 --> 00:26:35,790
I could've welcomed you downstairs if you
had told me about your visit earlier.

573
00:26:35,790 --> 00:26:36,350
It's fine.

574
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:37,070
Sorry for the poor reception.

575
00:26:37,070 --> 00:26:37,670
It's fine.

576
00:26:39,030 --> 00:26:39,830
Captain Wang.

577
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:43,180
-Mr. Lang.
-Officer...

578
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,210
Does this watch look familiar?

579
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:49,950
It's my watch.

580
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:52,920
Why are the police
looking into this watch?

581
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:54,380
I'd like to know that, too.

582
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:56,270
Why don't you tell me?

583
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:01,340
Well, I...

584
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:02,880
I lost it to Yibo when we were

585
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:03,830
playing a game.

586
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:06,960
Losing something

587
00:27:07,070 --> 00:27:09,330
to a friend isn't against the law, right?

588
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:13,380
Did you have this watch

589
00:27:14,110 --> 00:27:15,440
on the day Lu Zheng died?

590
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,580
Wait, Mr. Rong.

591
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,000
Even if the police know

592
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,060
this watch is mine,

593
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,550
they won't link Lu Zheng's case

594
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:26,740
to us.

595
00:27:26,830 --> 00:27:27,480
That depends

596
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,010
on what you tell the police.

597
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:30,920
Bowen.

598
00:27:32,030 --> 00:27:32,830
Some money is

599
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,370
not taken for nothing.

600
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,490
It looks very familiar.

601
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:40,960
This watch is a limited edition.

602
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,290
I have an identical one,

603
00:27:42,550 --> 00:27:44,150
but I gave it to someone else.

604
00:27:44,750 --> 00:27:46,080
Let's sit down and talk.

605
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,480
This

606
00:27:49,550 --> 00:27:50,820
should be my watch.

607
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:51,400
Really?

608
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:53,750
You gave it away? To whom?

609
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,680
Whoever you got this watch from,

610
00:27:59,110 --> 00:28:00,370
that's who I gave it to.

611
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,510
We got this

612
00:28:05,510 --> 00:28:06,970
from a fugitive on the run.

613
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:10,610
Mr. Lang, you have ties to a fugitive?

614
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,300
Wait, officers,

615
00:28:13,330 --> 00:28:14,790
you can't joke about this.

616
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,310
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

617
00:28:16,310 --> 00:28:17,590
How could I possibly have ties

618
00:28:17,590 --> 00:28:18,400
to a fugitive?

619
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,050
Could it be that

620
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,240
the person I gave it to

621
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,880
gave it to someone else?

622
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:26,340
Even if he didn't give it away,

623
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:27,710
could he have lost it?

624
00:28:28,030 --> 00:28:29,750
Right? E-Even if it wasn't lost,

625
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:31,210
it could have been stolen.

626
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,160
Well, there are many possibilities.

627
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:34,400
It's just that you probably can't remember

628
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,400
who you gave it to.

629
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,350
They all have poor memories.

630
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:37,790
Yeah.

631
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,610
Do you remember when you gave it away?

632
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:45,030
It's been a few months.

633
00:28:46,070 --> 00:28:46,510
No,

634
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,060
almost half a year.

635
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:50,470
Half a year ago, Chief Lu

636
00:28:50,590 --> 00:28:52,030
died in a car accident.

637
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,350
Do you know about this?

638
00:28:53,350 --> 00:28:54,000
Yes, I do.

639
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:55,880
What a pity.

640
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:58,550
What?

641
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:01,320
Is Chief Lu's accidental death

642
00:29:01,590 --> 00:29:02,880
related to this watch?

643
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:05,420
I say they're related.

644
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,400
The night Chief Lu

645
00:29:15,030 --> 00:29:16,230
had the car accident,

646
00:29:16,750 --> 00:29:18,150
I was indeed at the scene.

647
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:21,400
Yes.

648
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:24,260
The watch was on my wrist at that time.

649
00:29:25,850 --> 00:29:26,980
What a coincidence.

650
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:28,640
When Chief Lu had the accident,

651
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,440
you were right at the scene?

652
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,700
Yes, I was at the scene.

653
00:29:30,790 --> 00:29:32,200
Sanjiangkou is not a big place.

654
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,260
I just happened to pass by that night.

655
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:36,370
There are security cameras on that road,

656
00:29:36,370 --> 00:29:36,800
right?

657
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:37,590
Yes, there are.

658
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:38,160
I see.

659
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:40,070
You must have seen

660
00:29:40,110 --> 00:29:41,880
this special watch
on the surveillance cameras

661
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:42,590
and then found out

662
00:29:42,590 --> 00:29:43,680
that the owner of the watch was me,

663
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:44,680
so you came to ask me,

664
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:45,080
right?

665
00:29:48,550 --> 00:29:50,290
You were at the scene
of Chief Lu's car accident.

666
00:29:50,290 --> 00:29:50,830
Why didn't you

667
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:51,790
call the police immediately?

668
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:54,250
Because someone already called the police.

669
00:29:54,750 --> 00:29:55,720
It's been half a year.

670
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:59,270
The driver who caused the accident
should've been sentenced, right?

671
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:01,220
Or did you find out some connection

672
00:30:01,250 --> 00:30:03,510
between the driver and me, Captain Wang?

673
00:30:05,510 --> 00:30:06,910
Is there any connection?

674
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:10,910
Is there any connection?

675
00:30:11,030 --> 00:30:11,570
Nope.

676
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:13,660
Well, then,

677
00:30:13,830 --> 00:30:14,610
officers,

678
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:16,350
if you have any other questions,

679
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,510
I will answer them honestly

680
00:30:17,510 --> 00:30:19,170
and fully cooperate with you.

681
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,000
Do you have any other questions?

682
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:26,930
I'm done asking.

683
00:30:27,510 --> 00:30:28,370
Then that's it.

684
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,510
We'll find you if there's anything.

685
00:30:29,510 --> 00:30:30,070
Okay.

686
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:32,430
Won't you sit for a bit longer?

687
00:30:32,430 --> 00:30:33,180
No, thanks.

688
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:34,310
Then I'll see you out.

689
00:30:34,310 --> 00:30:34,750
Don't bother.

690
00:30:34,750 --> 00:30:35,400
Don't bother seeing us out.

691
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,400
Let me see you out.

692
00:30:36,830 --> 00:30:37,560
Take it slow.

693
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:42,680
Take care, Chief Zhang.

694
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:06,270
We didn't get any information out of him.

695
00:31:06,270 --> 00:31:07,670
But you seem quite happy.

696
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,420
The Chief must have a plan.

697
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,640
We asked everything we needed to, right?

698
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,160
We did.

699
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,000
Did we get the results we wanted?

700
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:28,480
No.

701
00:31:31,110 --> 00:31:32,400
Why can't a non-answer

702
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:35,110
count as an answer in itself?

703
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,170
What did Lang Bowen answer?

704
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:46,960
Okay.

705
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:50,400
The Municipal Bureau

706
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,880
checked Lang Bowen's call records.

707
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:53,070
On the day of Captain Ye's accident,

708
00:31:53,070 --> 00:31:54,800
he received a call from Lu Yibo.

709
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:55,620
The call was

710
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,640
made that night

711
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:57,550
at 9:53 p.m,

712
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,400
which lasted 25 seconds.

713
00:32:00,970 --> 00:32:02,430
Captain Ye must have found

714
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,040
clues about Chief Lu's case.

715
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,800
Lang Bowen was the murderer?

716
00:32:07,340 --> 00:32:08,890
He killed Chief Lu and then

717
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,360
silenced Captain Ye?

718
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:13,490
So,

719
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,360
Lang Bowen's denial

720
00:32:16,070 --> 00:32:17,270
is also an admission.

721
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:19,920
What an old fox.

722
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,700
He won't give up until he sees the coffin.

723
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,390
Then,

724
00:32:24,630 --> 00:32:25,960
push him a bit more

725
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,090
towards the coffin.

726
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:28,790
Ask the bureau

727
00:32:28,790 --> 00:32:30,190
to send cars to pick us up.

728
00:32:30,790 --> 00:32:31,270
Two.

729
00:32:35,730 --> 00:32:37,040
We drove here.

730
00:32:37,310 --> 00:32:39,240
Your car doesn't have that effect.

731
00:32:41,550 --> 00:32:42,810
What's wrong with you?

732
00:32:43,590 --> 00:32:44,760
Were you eavesdropping at the door again?

733
00:32:44,710 --> 00:32:47,770
[Century Otto]

734
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,030
I wasn't.

735
00:32:46,070 --> 00:32:47,800
Then why aren't you going home?

736
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:52,680
Bowen,

737
00:32:53,750 --> 00:32:54,830
I'm in my 20s.

738
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:55,680
You can't always

739
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:56,880
treat me like a child.

740
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:58,480
No matter what happens,

741
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,350
let's face it together,

742
00:32:59,350 --> 00:32:59,790
okay?

743
00:32:59,790 --> 00:33:00,680
Face what?

744
00:33:02,270 --> 00:33:04,000
You are facing a bright future,

745
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:05,520
a new life!

746
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:07,400
I will deal with

747
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,860
this mess in Sanjiangkou.

748
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,110
I can't let you

749
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:11,240
bear this alone.

750
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:13,200
The police already found you.

751
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:13,830
And those things

752
00:33:13,830 --> 00:33:15,560
you did with Mr. Rong before...

753
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:18,040
What nonsense are you talking about?

754
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,030
Didn't I tell you not to get involved

755
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:19,960
in our business?

756
00:33:24,950 --> 00:33:27,010
Do you think that's possible, Bowen?

757
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:28,680
I'm important to you.

758
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:30,740
But you matter even more to me, Bowen.

759
00:33:40,270 --> 00:33:41,800
Yangyang, you've grown up.

760
00:33:45,790 --> 00:33:46,680
Trust me.

761
00:33:47,110 --> 00:33:48,140
Think carefully.

762
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:49,510
Since you were little,

763
00:33:49,510 --> 00:33:50,750
have you ever seen me

764
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:52,200
fail to solve anything?

765
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:53,630
Have you?

766
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:55,680
Do you believe me?

767
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:57,590
Do you?

768
00:33:59,550 --> 00:34:00,750
I believe you, Bowen.

769
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:05,030
I got a gift for you.

770
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,320
I've wanted to give it to you
for a long time.

771
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,320
What is it, Bowen?

772
00:34:14,030 --> 00:34:15,510
When you are out alone,

773
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:16,880
especially in a foreign country,

774
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:17,550
this is

775
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:18,360
directly related

776
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:19,760
to your personal safety.

777
00:34:23,510 --> 00:34:24,230
A gun?

778
00:34:27,350 --> 00:34:28,880
[Ultra-thin] [Try-out pack]

779
00:34:29,510 --> 00:34:29,880
Wait, Bowen,

780
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,030
why did you buy these for me?

781
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:32,070
So you recognize them.

782
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:32,469
Good.

783
00:34:32,489 --> 00:34:33,820
Then I can rest assured.

784
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,520
You know how to use them, huh?

785
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:36,850
This is my privacy.

786
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:39,400
Talking about privacy with me?

787
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:40,550
Your bare-bottom photos

788
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:41,670
are still on my phone.

789
00:34:41,670 --> 00:34:42,130
Take it.

790
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:45,000
Use them sparingly.

791
00:34:46,110 --> 00:34:46,639
Let's go.

792
00:34:48,110 --> 00:34:49,480
Let's tell Mom and Dad the good news.

793
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:50,190
Let's go.

794
00:34:51,070 --> 00:34:51,510
Wait, wait.

795
00:34:51,510 --> 00:34:52,639
D-Don't bring this.

796
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:53,320
Right.

797
00:34:55,830 --> 00:35:01,010
[Century Otto]

798
00:34:57,150 --> 00:34:58,030
What happened?

799
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,230
No idea.

800
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:01,280
Why didn't they arrest that bastard?

801
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,550
It's only a matter of time.

802
00:35:02,550 --> 00:35:04,370
For thugs like him,

803
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:06,210
even if they become big bosses,

804
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:08,470
most of them
can't get through an investigation.

805
00:35:08,470 --> 00:35:10,200
Can their background be clean?

806
00:35:10,550 --> 00:35:12,110
You can't put it so absolutely.

807
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,040
Is Lang Bowen definitely a bad guy?

808
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:15,300
He's so rich now.

809
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:16,880
Can't he turn over a new leaf?

810
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:18,470
What if he's helping the police
solve a case?

811
00:35:18,470 --> 00:35:19,400
It's hard to say.

812
00:35:20,710 --> 00:35:22,550
Don't let the masses make random guesses.

813
00:35:22,550 --> 00:35:24,070
Without solid evidence,

814
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:26,930
the police won't arrest people
for no reason.

815
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:28,810
Let's go.

816
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:43,070
[Police]

817
00:35:47,710 --> 00:35:49,000
We got some news from the bank

818
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:49,840
this morning.

819
00:35:50,590 --> 00:35:52,360
Three days after Chief Lu's accident,

820
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,110
Rongcheng Group

821
00:35:53,110 --> 00:35:54,400
transferred 30 million yuan

822
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:55,860
to Otto for project funds.

823
00:35:58,510 --> 00:36:00,510
Otto and Rongcheng Group are

824
00:36:00,550 --> 00:36:02,950
in an upstream-downstream relationship.

825
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,060
One acquires land,

826
00:36:04,670 --> 00:36:06,070
one handles demolition.

827
00:36:06,150 --> 00:36:08,550
Their financial transactions are normal.

828
00:36:08,630 --> 00:36:09,840
But wasn't the timing

829
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,170
a bit too coincidental?

830
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:13,760
That means

831
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,970
this money

832
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:16,480
might be of other uses.

833
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:17,840
Possibly.

834
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:20,710
And possibly not.

835
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,410
We'll find out soon enough.

836
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:24,760
Officer Song,

837
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,620
the tow truck has arrived at Otto.

838
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,300
Why did you get a tow truck?

839
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:29,930
Didn't your car break down?

840
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:32,590
Li Qian,

841
00:36:32,590 --> 00:36:33,780
explain it to him.

842
00:36:34,110 --> 00:36:35,510
We just asked Lang Bowen

843
00:36:35,510 --> 00:36:36,710
about the situation.

844
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:38,280
He didn't tell us a single shred of truth

845
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:39,630
and acted very arrogantly.

846
00:36:39,630 --> 00:36:40,560
That's for sure.

847
00:36:40,630 --> 00:36:41,360
People like him

848
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,510
won't give up until he sees the coffin.

849
00:36:42,510 --> 00:36:43,670
So we need you.

850
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:46,930
What do you mean?

851
00:36:47,510 --> 00:36:48,920
You came to pick us up

852
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,360
so ostentatiously just now.

853
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:51,490
If Lang Bowen knows,

854
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:53,440
Zhou Rong will definitely know.

855
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:54,670
If they have something shady
hidden in their hearts,

856
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:55,930
they will take action.

857
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,250
This is sowing discord.

858
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,410
As long as they move,

859
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:00,610
we'll have a chance.

860
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:02,130
Keep a close eye on them.

861
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:02,880
Understood.

862
00:37:05,110 --> 00:37:07,110
We don't need the tow truck. Thanks.

863
00:37:23,550 --> 00:37:25,370
Stop running around!

864
00:37:25,450 --> 00:37:27,180
Aren't you tired? Stand still!

865
00:37:40,030 --> 00:37:41,030
Fall!

866
00:37:43,630 --> 00:37:44,840
Fall down!

867
00:37:57,720 --> 00:37:58,660
Can you find

868
00:37:58,880 --> 00:37:59,550
someone less tough

869
00:37:59,550 --> 00:38:00,660
to beat next time?

870
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:01,440
Okay.

871
00:38:01,590 --> 00:38:03,190
I'll spar with you next time.

872
00:38:08,150 --> 00:38:08,680
Mr. Rong.

873
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:09,360
What?

874
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:10,490
It's... It's itchy!

875
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:16,670
Zhang Yi'ang

876
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,140
went to see Lang Bowen.

877
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:20,720
Who said that?

878
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:21,840
Li Penggai.

879
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,360
He saw it with his own eyes

880
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,890
when he was passing by Otto.

881
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:26,710
What's wrong

882
00:38:27,710 --> 00:38:28,770
with Zhang Yi'ang?

883
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,940
I gave him my business card

884
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:31,800
and told him to call me

885
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:33,060
if he needed anything.

886
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:34,660
But he never called me.

887
00:38:35,550 --> 00:38:36,750
Why is he interacting

888
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:38,940
with Lu Yibo and Lang Bowen

889
00:38:39,070 --> 00:38:40,000
so often?

890
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:42,690
What is he doing?

891
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:44,590
Mr. Rong,

892
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:46,810
should we do something?

893
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,000
What do you want to do?

894
00:38:50,670 --> 00:38:51,670
Kill someone?

895
00:38:52,670 --> 00:38:54,730
Even a swine wouldn't be this stupid.

896
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,860
There's no need to make a big fuss.

897
00:38:58,760 --> 00:38:59,510
The police

898
00:39:00,150 --> 00:39:01,880
just want to test us right now.

899
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:04,320
If we do something, we'll make a mistake.

900
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:05,320
If we do nothing,

901
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:07,230
we'll be safe.

902
00:39:08,110 --> 00:39:09,450
I'm just worried.

903
00:39:09,590 --> 00:39:10,850
Bowen is an honest man.

904
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:11,800
If he says anything

905
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:12,550
unfavorable to you,

906
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:14,610
wouldn't we be in a passive position?

907
00:39:14,670 --> 00:39:15,150
He...

908
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,630
He wouldn't dare.

909
00:39:19,670 --> 00:39:20,400
Understood.

910
00:39:22,550 --> 00:39:23,270
Mr. Rong,

911
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:25,710
Li Penggai
made a great contribution this time.

912
00:39:25,710 --> 00:39:26,370
Do you think

913
00:39:26,550 --> 00:39:28,240
we should let him come back?

914
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:29,700
Where did he go?

915
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,190
He went to transport sand.

916
00:39:31,190 --> 00:39:32,790
Why is he transporting sand?

917
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:33,630
He's a good boy.

918
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:34,630
Let him come back.

919
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:36,070
T-Then I'll just...

920
00:39:36,070 --> 00:39:36,550
Go, go.

921
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:38,820
Fetch me my bag.

922
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:39,710
Okay.

923
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,990
Run a few steps.

924
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:02,150
Hello?

925
00:40:03,190 --> 00:40:03,880
It's me.
